list.name: Changes
list.comment:
Refactor workspace.xml and update tasks
The workspace.xml file has been refactored to include new tasks and update old ones. Focus was on enhancing the workspace configurations, modifying commit descriptions, and adding Azure publishing settings. Additional changes have been made to ensure better webpage layout positioning in site.css file as well.

task.summary:
Remove .idea workspace configuration file
The .idea workspace.xml configuration file was deleted to avoid sharing of personal IDE settings. This file is generated automatically by the IDE and should not be included in version control as it contains user specific settings. This change will improve project portability across different development environments.

Add new skills to Parameters.cs
The commit expands the number of skills in the SkillModel section by adding .NET CORE, Google, Azure, React and Javascript. Each skill model includes a skill name, description, and an associated icon URL.

Update skill display and input placeholder in Home view
The skill details display has been updated in the Home view to be more comprehensible by separating the skill name and description into separate spans. Furthermore, the placeholder text of the Name input field under 'Contact Me' form has been updated to "Enter your name" aiming for better clarity.

Update skill display and input placeholder in Home view
The skill details display has been updated in the Home view to be more comprehensible by separating the skill name and description into separate spans. Furthermore, the placeholder text of the Name input field under 'Contact Me' form has been updated to "Enter your name" aiming for better clarity.

Add shelved patch for uncommitted changes
This commit adds a new shelved.patch file capturing the uncommitted changes in the project. This patch serves as a backup of these uncommitted changes to allow switching branches or updates without losing current progress.

Update footer with additional details and links
The footer layout has been updated to include more detailed information like the name and address. Social links are now also dynamic, deriving from the @Parameters object rather than being hardcoded.

Update text style in Github project title
The Github project title in the shared project box view has been updated with new CSS styles for font size and font weight. Additionally, the title is now transformed to uppercase for better visual impact.

Update navigation bar in shared view
The navigation bar in the shared view file "_Navbar.cshtml" has been modified. The "Home" link and title have been replaced with dynamic weather information. The "Hire Me" section is also updated to a "Contact Me" call-to-action button.

Update default value for Message in ContactMeModel
The default message string in the ContactMeModel has been updated in order to be more appealing and professional. This new message is designed to encourage potential candidates to respond more effectively.

Update project descriptions and images in DataInitializer
In this commit, the project descriptions in the DataInitializer class have been updated to provide more layout for each project. Additionally, the project images' URLs have been updated to point to a .webp version instead of a .png for improved loading speed. A new project 'RESTful API' has also been added to the list of projects.

Update weather description in HomeController
The hardcoded weather description was updated in two instances within the HomeController file. The description was changed from "Warm as hell" to "TOO HOT!".

Updated styling and structure on several sections of the homepage
In this update, the layout of homepage elements was adjusted to improve appearance and HTML semantics. The typography was modified capital letters on labels and headers for clarity. Looping adjustments also made for more efficient rendering of data, such as references and skills.

Update nullability in IndexViewModel properties
Good code structure was enforced by updating the nullability of some properties inside the IndexViewModel class. The WeatherModel, GithubProjectModels, and ListOfSkills properties have been updated to have a nullable type instead of an initially null object.

Add new parameters for website content
Added links to resume and several development skills icons to the Parameters.cs file. Additionally, a list of reference quotes has been included for future use. These updates enhance the site content, providing more detailed professional information.

Simplify Program.cs by removing unnecessary imports and code
This commit removes several unnecessary 'using' imports that weren't being utilized within Project-2's Program.cs file. Additionally, the HTTP request pipeline configuration was simplified and unneeded conditionals were discarded, now all environments use MigrationEndPoint, ExceptionHandler and Hsts.

Update CSS styles, add new font and improve interactivity
The main changes in this commit include altering many CSS properties to modify the site's aesthetics. A new font, Rubik, has been imported and used across the site replacing the previous one. User interactivity has been improved by adding hover and active styles to buttons, as well as focus styles to input fields. Some new CSS classes have been created for additional features and unnecessary styles were removed.

Update workspace configuration and site aesthetics
This commit primarily refines workspace.xml file and updates site aesthetics in site.css. The workspace file now includes detailed commit messages that better describe the recent changes. The site's design has been enhanced by altering many CSS styles, including modifying button styles and structure of several sections in the homepage. Lastly, a new font, Rubik, has been incorporated across the site.

Refactor home page HTML for better readability
This commit simplifies sections of the home page HTML to improve readability and maintainability. It condenses paragraphs into one and removes inline styling for buttons, replacing them with an id value for CSS targeting. Changed the placeholder text to uppercase for better user visibility.

Convert project description to uppercase in project box
The project description in the GitHub project box view has been updated to display in uppercase. This alteration improves visibility and alignment with other UI elements.

Update footer content and styles
Altered the styling of the footer in _Footer.cshtml, including an increase in line-height for better readability. Updated the footer's content to improve the visibility and accessibility of key information such as address and email.

Update workspace configuration and enhance site aesthetics
This commit entails modifications to the workspace.xml and site.css files. Changes include an update of commit messages in the workspace file for better change descriptions. Site aesthetics have been enhanced, including updated button styles & homepage sections structures, and the introduction of a new font, Rubik, across the site.

task.summary:
Refactor Github project service and update project details
This commit includes removal of the unused Get method in IGithubProjectService interface and GithubApiService class. The HomeController's submit method has been updated to use latitude and longitude for weather service, and the email body message has been localized. Finally, a new workspace.xml file has been added.

Update workspace configurations and refactor CSS files
Adjusted workspace configurations in workspace.xml file, including changes in commit descriptions, and added Azure publishing settings. Also updated site.css for better webpage layout positioning by implementing CSS grid and transform properties.

Update workspace configuration and enhance site aesthetics
This commit includes changes in workspace.xml file with updated commit descriptions and additional Azure publishing settings. Modification in site.css allows better webpage layout positioning. A few new quotes have also been added to the Parameters in the Infrastructure folder.

Update workspace.xml and site.css files
The workspace.xml file was updated, adding Azure publishing settings and modifying commit descriptions. Webpage layout positioning was also improved via changes in the site.css file. A few new quotes have been added to the Parameters in the Infrastructure folder.
